.TH "ipi_send_single" 9 "ipi_send_single" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ipi_send_single \- Send an IPI to a single CPU
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ipi_send_single
.BI "(unsigned int virq "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cpu "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "virq" 12
linux irq number from \fBirq_reserve_ipi\fP
.IP "cpu" 12
destination CPU, must in the destination mask passed to
\fBirq_reserve_ipi\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns zero on success and negative error number on failure.
